    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix CQI indication vendor extension handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `pack_cqi_indication` function in nfapi_p7.c was incorrectly setting the vendor extension to NULL before processing, causing loss of vendor extension data in CQI indications. This fix removes the erroneous NULL assignment to allow proper vendor extension handling.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Removed line that set `pNfapiMsg->vendor_extension=NULL` in `pack_cqi_indication` function\n- The function now properly passes through vendor extension data like other similar indication functions\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running OAI with vendor extensions enabled, CQI indications were missing vendor extension data that should have been included in the packed message. This manifested as missing custom fields in the CQI reports sent from the PHY to the MAC layer.\n\nThe issue can be reproduced by:\n1. Enabling vendor extensions in the NFAPI configuration\n2. Generating CQI reports with vendor-specific data\n3. Observing that the vendor extension data is not present in the packed CQI indication message\n\nAfter this fix, vendor extension data should properly appear in CQI indication messages.\n"
}